  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed House amended",
    "asOf": "2009-05-19",
    "date": "2009-06-02T21:27:13Z",
    "text": "Directs the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to make grants to encourage the development of new assistive technologies for specially adapted housing for disabled veterans. Limits grant amounts to $200,000 annually per recipient.\n\nProvides that if a grant recipient is awarded a patent related to assistive technology developed with grant amounts, the Secretary shall retain no less than a 30% interest in the patent.\n\nProvides grant funds. Terminates grant authority five years after the enactment of this Act."
  },
